
# 📱 Student Behavioral Study: Social Media Addiction Metrics

## 📌 1. Project Background & Problem Statement
With the global rise of algorithm-driven social platforms, digital dependency among students has expanded dramatically. For corporate HR teams, data-driven wellness institutions, and academic directors, the primary challenge is identifying the point where healthy daily connectivity degrades into a psychological and behavioral addiction risk.

**The Core Challenge:** This project analyzes structured survey data from a global cohort of 705 student profiles. It isolates how prolonged daily social media screen time triggers a negative cascade into compromised sleep patterns, localized social friction, falling mental health scores, and drops in academic performance.

